1
00:00:30,663 --> 00:00:33,131
<i>We've put an explosive charge
in your head.</i>

2
00:00:39,338 --> 00:00:41,033
Does that sound familiar?

3
00:00:44,277 --> 00:00:46,472
The Rabbit's Foot. Where is it?

4
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,207
I gave it to you.

5
00:00:49,348 --> 00:00:52,340
Ethan, where's the Rabbit's Foot?

6
00:00:53,019 --> 00:00:56,216
Wait... What are you saying?
That wasn't it?

7
00:00:56,789 --> 00:00:59,986
- What I gave you, was that...
- I'm going to count to 10.

8
00:01:00,092 --> 00:01:04,153
You're going to tell me
where the Rabbit's Foot is or she dies.

9
00:01:12,204 --> 00:01:14,570
Jules, it's going to be okay.

10
00:01:15,741 --> 00:01:18,335
It's going to be okay.
Do you understand?

11
00:01:19,478 --> 00:01:20,604
One.

12
00:01:20,880 --> 00:01:24,008
You listen to me.
I got exactly what you asked for.

13
00:01:24,116 --> 00:01:26,380
Did you want something else?

14
00:01:26,919 --> 00:01:28,648
If there was a misunderstanding,
I will fix it.

15
00:01:28,754 --> 00:01:30,654
I can get it, whatever you want.

16
00:01:30,756 --> 00:01:31,916
Two.

17
00:01:32,425 --> 00:01:35,451
Listen. Talk to me. We can talk,

18
00:01:35,795 --> 00:01:37,353
like gentlemen.

19
00:01:39,265 --> 00:01:41,290
- Three.
- God!

20
00:01:50,476 --> 00:01:53,104
All right. All right, all right.

21
00:01:54,647 --> 00:01:57,138
I know where the Rabbit's Foot is.

22
00:01:58,351 --> 00:01:59,477
I can help you.

23
00:01:59,585 --> 00:02:02,247
The way you helped me
on the airplane?

24
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:04,017
That way?

25
00:02:04,523 --> 00:02:07,048
You put the gun down.
I'm not talking to you like this.

26
00:02:07,159 --> 00:02:09,593
That's your choice. Four.

27
00:02:10,997 --> 00:02:12,555
The Rabbit's Foot's in Paris.

28
00:02:12,665 --> 00:02:15,395
You want to know where in Paris?
Then let her go.

29
00:02:15,501 --> 00:02:18,595
- 'Cause you will not...
- It's not in Paris. Five.

30
00:02:20,506 --> 00:02:22,133
I can get it for you.

31
00:02:22,241 --> 00:02:24,141
But you kill her, you do this,
you get nothing.

32
00:02:24,243 --> 00:02:26,473
- Six.
- Are you listening to me?

33
00:02:26,579 --> 00:02:29,742
The only way you're going
to get what you want is for you to...

34
00:02:29,849 --> 00:02:31,942
- Do you think I'm playing?
- Son of a bitch!

35
00:02:32,051 --> 00:02:34,383
Do you think I'm playing?
You don't think I'll do it?

36
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:36,318
Where is it? Where the hell is it?

37
00:02:36,422 --> 00:02:37,889
- Look at me.
- Where the hell is it?

38
00:02:37,990 --> 00:02:40,390
- Stay with me.
- Seven! Seven!

39
00:02:40,526 --> 00:02:45,020
I am going to kill you.
I swear to God I'm going to kill you!

40
00:02:45,164 --> 00:02:47,189
- Eight!
- No, please.

41
00:02:52,438 --> 00:02:56,033
Please. Don't do this. Just let her go.

42
00:02:57,677 --> 00:03:00,976
I promise you. I promise you.

43
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,742
- I can figure out how to get whatever...
- Nine.

44
00:03:04,917 --> 00:03:07,044
Listen to me. Listen to me.

45
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:10,518
I want to help you.

46
00:03:10,790 --> 00:03:13,350
I want to help you get
whatever you want.

47
00:03:13,459 --> 00:03:17,156
But you got to do what's right.
What you know is right.

48
00:03:23,402 --> 00:03:26,030
No. No.

49
00:03:29,775 --> 00:03:30,833
No.

50
00:03:30,943 --> 00:03:31,655
- Ten.
- Don't!

51
00:03:31,690 --> 00:03:32,368
- Ten.
- Don't!

52
00:04:10,649 --> 00:04:12,583
- What are you doing?
- Your brother wants another one.

53
00:04:12,685 --> 00:04:14,346
Oh, God, no.
Ethan, that's what we talked about...

54
00:04:14,453 --> 00:04:16,421
- I'm watching him. He's fine.
- That's how it is with Rick.

55
00:04:16,522 --> 00:04:19,082
He's fine and then suddenly he's naked
and he's hugging everybody.

56
00:04:19,191 --> 00:04:22,058
- I'll take full responsibility for Rick.
- You will? Full?

57
00:04:22,161 --> 00:04:24,652
- Well, mostly full.
- It's a huge responsibility.

58
00:04:24,764 --> 00:04:26,322
It's going well, right?

59
00:04:26,432 --> 00:04:28,730
- It's going really well.
- Yeah.

60
00:04:29,869 --> 00:04:31,564
Julia, your sister's here.

61
00:04:32,004 --> 00:04:34,472
- Give me a hug.
- You look so beautiful.

62
00:04:34,607 --> 00:04:36,666
I don't know about that. So, is this him?

63
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:39,404
- I hope so.
- Oh, come here. Oh, gosh.

64
00:04:40,279 --> 00:04:42,076
All right. Mom's dying to see you.

65
00:04:42,181 --> 00:04:44,206
I can't believe
you guys came all the way to Virginia.

66
00:04:44,316 --> 00:04:45,544
Like we'd miss your engagement...

67
00:04:45,651 --> 00:04:49,485
When Julia called and told me
that she was getting married,

68
00:04:49,622 --> 00:04:52,591
I had one thought,
that it was just too bad

69
00:04:53,659 --> 00:04:56,958
that Daddy wasn't here
to walk her down the aisle.

70
00:04:57,530 --> 00:05:00,294
And then when Julia told me...
Thanks, Mom.

71
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:02,867
That Ethan doesn't have
his parents anymore, either,

72
00:05:02,968 --> 00:05:04,765
I got really sad.

73
00:05:04,870 --> 00:05:09,034
But it occurred to me
that this is about starting a new family

74
00:05:09,341 --> 00:05:11,104
and how beautiful that is.

75
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:14,338
And I just want to say
I am making Julia an aunt,

76
00:05:14,480 --> 00:05:17,278
so I expect the same treatment
very, very soon.

77
00:05:17,383 --> 00:05:18,645
Cheers!

78
00:05:24,356 --> 00:05:25,653
Department of Transportation?

79
00:05:25,758 --> 00:05:27,953
I've been there over 10 years now.
Wow.

80
00:05:28,060 --> 00:05:29,618
What do you do at the DOT?

81
00:05:29,728 --> 00:05:31,252
I study traffic patterns.

82
00:05:31,363 --> 00:05:33,661
You hit the brakes for a second,
just tap them on the freeway,

83
00:05:33,766 --> 00:05:35,631
you can literally track
the ripple effect of that action

84
00:05:35,734 --> 00:05:37,258
across a 200-mile stretch of road,

85
00:05:37,369 --> 00:05:38,666
because traffic has a memory.

86
00:05:38,771 --> 00:05:40,762
It's amazing. It's like a living organism.

87
00:05:40,873 --> 00:05:42,568
Freshen that up for you?
What is it, vodka martini?

88
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:43,767
Yeah. Thanks.

89
00:05:43,876 --> 00:05:45,810
Ladies, do you need...

90
00:05:49,281 --> 00:05:50,839
- I'd marry him.
- I would, too.

91
00:05:50,950 --> 00:05:53,783
Okay, so, a three-week
heli-boarding honeymoon?

92
00:05:53,919 --> 00:05:56,820
- Okay, you actually get dropped...
- From a helicopter, yeah.

93
00:05:56,922 --> 00:05:58,890
- It's how they met.
- Really?

94
00:05:58,991 --> 00:06:00,856
- Tell her the story.
- There's no story.

95
00:06:00,960 --> 00:06:02,552
It is a good story. Tell the story.

96
00:06:02,661 --> 00:06:05,721
First of all,
no one was ever good enough for Julia.

97
00:06:05,831 --> 00:06:07,059
Oh, here we go.

98
00:06:07,166 --> 00:06:11,102
Not spontaneous enough,
adventurous enough, funny enough...

99
00:06:11,237 --> 00:06:14,001
You know what? No, that's not true.
You make it sound like I've never dated.

100
00:06:14,106 --> 00:06:15,130
No one we liked.

101
00:06:15,241 --> 00:06:17,038
- That is true.
- That is true.

102
00:06:31,090 --> 00:06:34,423
Then she goes and gets in a chopper
that takes off from this lake...

103
00:06:34,526 --> 00:06:37,324
- What was the name of that lake?
- Lake...

104
00:06:38,330 --> 00:06:40,798
Lake Wanaka. Wanaka.

105
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:43,295
Wanaka. Thank you.

106
00:06:44,470 --> 00:06:46,165
- Oh, he heard that?
- How did he hear that?

107
00:06:46,272 --> 00:06:48,240
And the hospital's cool
with you taking three weeks?

108
00:06:48,340 --> 00:06:51,332
Yeah, I'm not the only nurse
employed there, you know.

109
00:07:17,002 --> 00:07:19,300
I'm psyched that you're going
to be my brother, man.

110
00:07:19,405 --> 00:07:20,429
So am I, Rick.

111
00:07:20,539 --> 00:07:22,404
No, it's awesome.
I think it's going to be sick.

112
00:07:22,508 --> 00:07:24,908
Me, too, man.
I just got to get the phone.

113
00:07:25,010 --> 00:07:26,841
- You rock hard.
- Okay.

114
00:07:27,913 --> 00:07:28,971
Hello?

115
00:07:29,081 --> 00:07:31,174
<i>- Is this Mr. Ethan Hunt?
- Yes, it is.</i>

116
00:07:31,317 --> 00:07:33,785
<i>This is Ready-Travel Resort Services.</i>

117
00:07:33,886 --> 00:07:38,516
<i>We'd like to offer you a chance to win
an all-expense-paid trip to Mexico.</i>

118
00:07:57,209 --> 00:07:59,234
We ran out of ice.
I'll be back in 10 minutes.

119
00:07:59,345 --> 00:08:01,609
- Oh, no. Can't somebody else go?
- No, I got it.

120
00:08:01,714 --> 00:08:03,648
I'll be right back. Hi, Betsy.

121
00:08:03,749 --> 00:08:05,080
Thank you.

122
00:08:22,768 --> 00:08:24,201
$1.86.

123
00:08:33,779 --> 00:08:37,579
Thanks for coming.
Can't decide what size Slurpee to get.

124
00:08:38,250 --> 00:08:40,684
I usually go for the 900-ouncer.

125
00:08:42,421 --> 00:08:45,049
How's that party? Sorry I had to call you.

126
00:08:45,157 --> 00:08:47,148
- Yeah, you should have come.
- You should have invited me.

127
00:08:47,259 --> 00:08:49,625
- You know I would have.
- Thanks.

128
00:08:52,131 --> 00:08:55,225
I know we joke about it, but I am always
this close to begging you

129
00:08:55,334 --> 00:08:57,700
to stop training our people
and get your ass back in the field.

130
00:08:57,803 --> 00:09:00,670
But that's not what you do anymore,
and so I respect that choice.

131
00:09:00,773 --> 00:09:04,903
You know I do. Family's everything.

132
00:09:07,146 --> 00:09:09,478
Come on, John. What's going on?

133
00:09:13,419 --> 00:09:15,148
It's Agent Farris.

134
00:09:15,754 --> 00:09:17,779
She was on an operation.

135
00:09:18,490 --> 00:09:21,926
She's disappeared.
Been off-grid 11 hours.

136
00:09:23,629 --> 00:09:27,565
I'm sending in Search and Rescue.
I was hoping you'd want in.

137
00:09:32,337 --> 00:09:34,703
You've got good people for that.

138
00:09:37,743 --> 00:09:40,337
Yeah. Yep, that we do.

139
00:09:40,913 --> 00:09:44,349
Wheels up at sunrise
if you have a change of heart.

140
00:09:44,917 --> 00:09:47,681
Take some pictures of the party for me.

141
00:10:07,406 --> 00:10:09,135
<i>Ethan. Three days ago,</i>

142
00:10:09,241 --> 00:10:12,733
<i>Agent Lindsey Farris was captured
while on a surveillance operation.</i>

143
00:10:12,845 --> 00:10:15,575
<i>This is the man she was tracking.
His name is Owen Davian.</i>

144
00:10:15,681 --> 00:10:16,978
<i>Details are eyes-only,</i>

145
00:10:17,082 --> 00:10:19,846
<i>but I can tell you
that Davian's a black-market trafficker.</i>

146
00:10:19,952 --> 00:10:22,853
<i>Extremely dangerous
and a priority for us.</i>

147
00:10:23,222 --> 00:10:24,917
<i>At 1400 hours today,</i>

148
00:10:25,057 --> 00:10:27,184
<i>a recon satellite ID'd
a caravan of vehicles</i>

149
00:10:27,292 --> 00:10:30,921
<i>with plates matching those known to
have been used by Davian's operatives.</i>

150
00:10:31,029 --> 00:10:33,589
<i>They stopped at a derelict factory
outside Berlin.</i>

151
00:10:33,699 --> 00:10:36,964
<i>It appears they have a hostage.
We believe it's Agent Farris.</i>

152
00:10:37,069 --> 00:10:39,162
<i>Normally we would disavow,</i>

153
00:10:39,271 --> 00:10:41,330
<i>but Lindsey may be the key
to getting us closer to Davian,</i>

154
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,135
<i>and that's a risk we need to take.</i>

155
00:10:43,242 --> 00:10:45,938
<i>Your mission,
should you choose to accept it,</i>

156
00:10:46,078 --> 00:10:48,603
<i>is to find Lindsey and bring her home.</i>

157
00:10:48,747 --> 00:10:50,977
<i>I've already assembled a team.</i>

158
00:10:51,817 --> 00:10:53,978
<i>I have them standing by,
awaiting your word.</i>

159
00:10:54,753 --> 00:10:59,053
<i>This message, let's call it
my excellent engagement gift to you,</i>

160
00:10:59,591 --> 00:11:01,218
<i>will self-destruct in five seconds.</i>

161
00:11:01,326 --> 00:11:03,920
<i>Good luck, Ethan, and thanks again.</i>

162
00:11:19,845 --> 00:11:21,039
<i>Am I ready?</i>

163
00:11:33,525 --> 00:11:35,925
- You okay?
- Yeah.

164
00:11:37,796 --> 00:11:39,058
Yeah.

165
00:11:52,311 --> 00:11:56,645
You know, I'm sorry. I realized
I didn't tell you that the office called

166
00:11:57,549 --> 00:11:59,949
during the party.
I have to go to Houston for a night.

167
00:12:00,052 --> 00:12:03,954
METRO's having
a public transpo conference.

168
00:12:07,025 --> 00:12:10,517
- It's so last-minute.
- I know.

169
00:12:37,256 --> 00:12:38,883
Well, well, well.

170
00:12:39,024 --> 00:12:42,653
Now, if it isn't
Mr. "Those Who Can't Do, Teach"

171
00:12:42,761 --> 00:12:44,285
back in the field.

172
00:12:44,396 --> 00:12:46,557
- What's up, baby?
- Hey, man.

173
00:12:47,432 --> 00:12:50,959
Hey, Ethan, don't worry.
We're going to get the girl.

174
00:12:51,503 --> 00:12:55,234
Or have you been away so long
you've forgotten how good we are?

175
00:12:56,575 --> 00:12:58,167
Welcome back, brother.

176
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:23,967
Is our truck in place?

177
00:13:24,102 --> 00:13:25,194
Weapons good to go?

178
00:13:25,304 --> 00:13:27,033
- Yeah. You?
- Yeah.

179
00:13:27,439 --> 00:13:29,100
You know I got your six.

180
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:31,641
Hey, man. That's your job.

181
00:13:53,465 --> 00:13:56,059
<i>Guns one, activated.
Guns two, activated.</i>

182
00:13:56,168 --> 00:13:59,160
<i>Guns three, activated.
Guns four, activated.</i>

183
00:14:00,205 --> 00:14:01,638
<i>Guns ready.</i>

184
00:14:07,779 --> 00:14:09,508
All four guns operational.

185
00:14:09,648 --> 00:14:13,311
They've got men on
the second, third, fourth floors.

186
00:14:14,019 --> 00:14:15,816
<i>I count 14 of them.</i>

187
00:14:16,955 --> 00:14:19,048
Observer, I'm in approach position.

188
00:14:19,157 --> 00:14:21,022
Roger that. Stand by.

189
00:14:26,198 --> 00:14:27,426
<i>Target match.</i>

190
00:14:27,532 --> 00:14:30,433
The prize is on the sixth floor.
Two Tangos with her.

191
00:14:30,802 --> 00:14:32,133
Moving in.

192
00:14:49,221 --> 00:14:50,779
<i>So, Raider One, at some point,</i>

193
00:14:50,889 --> 00:14:53,289
we got to go over
this whole "getting married" thing.

194
00:14:53,392 --> 00:14:55,189
Negative, Observer.

195
00:14:55,327 --> 00:14:58,125
I don't respect you nearly enough
to have that conversation.

196
00:14:58,230 --> 00:14:59,390
<i>You may not respect me,</i>

197
00:14:59,498 --> 00:15:01,625
<i>but for now you're stuck
with my voice in your head.</i>

198
00:15:01,733 --> 00:15:04,634
So, this girl,
what the hell do you see in her anyway?

199
00:15:04,736 --> 00:15:07,899
Who, Julia? You've never met her.

200
00:15:08,039 --> 00:15:10,906
Yeah, and the way things are,
I probably never will.

201
00:15:11,109 --> 00:15:14,078
<i>Lucky for her, right?
That's what you're thinking.</i>

202
00:15:14,579 --> 00:15:16,012
They've got communications gear.

203
00:15:16,114 --> 00:15:19,083
Two Tangos, second floor,
northwest corridor.

204
00:15:19,451 --> 00:15:20,918
Groundhog, that's you.

205
00:15:21,019 --> 00:15:22,646
<i>You need to grab that gear
on the second floor</i>

206
00:15:22,754 --> 00:15:24,119
<i>as soon as we go hot.</i>

207
00:15:24,222 --> 00:15:26,713
Copy that. I'll need two minutes,

208
00:15:27,192 --> 00:15:28,591
which means
you'll need me in one, right?

209
00:15:28,693 --> 00:15:30,251
Yeah, just about.

210
00:15:30,395 --> 00:15:32,693
Raider One,
make a left at the top of the stairs.

211
00:15:32,798 --> 00:15:35,733
<i>The prize should be
at the end of the hall.</i>

212
00:15:54,252 --> 00:15:56,379
Phoenix, I have eye on the prize.

213
00:15:56,488 --> 00:15:58,422
Give her 10 cc's more.

214
00:16:03,495 --> 00:16:05,861
- Call me when she wakes.
- Okay.

215
00:16:06,832 --> 00:16:08,561
We need touchdown in less than three.
Do you copy?

216
00:16:08,667 --> 00:16:10,100
<i>Roger that, I copy.</i>

217
00:16:10,235 --> 00:16:13,261
Please, when do I not copy?
All I do is copy.

218
00:16:17,609 --> 00:16:19,975
Stand by to go live. On my mark.

219
00:16:21,079 --> 00:16:22,205
<i>Three.</i>

220
00:16:22,314 --> 00:16:23,372
<i>Two.</i>

221
00:16:23,482 --> 00:16:25,211
One. Execute.

222
00:16:32,958 --> 00:16:36,121
<i>Warning. Warning.</i>

223
00:16:56,815 --> 00:16:58,783
Raider One, you're clear. Move!

224
00:17:05,657 --> 00:17:08,626
Lindsey. Lindsey.

225
00:17:10,328 --> 00:17:11,556
Ethan?

226
00:17:13,164 --> 00:17:15,189
I'm going to get you home.

227
00:17:19,771 --> 00:17:22,001
Observer, I've got the prize.
Evac in three.

228
00:17:22,107 --> 00:17:23,540
<i>Roger that.</i>

229
00:17:29,581 --> 00:17:33,210
This is adrenaline.
Lindsey, you're going to feel this.

230
00:17:49,968 --> 00:17:52,232
<i>Groundhog, second floor is clear.</i>

231
00:17:52,370 --> 00:17:53,837
On the move!

232
00:18:15,794 --> 00:18:18,763
Observer, we're on the move. Wrap out.

233
00:18:18,897 --> 00:18:21,058
<i>- Evac in 90 seconds.
- Roger that.</i>

234
00:18:21,166 --> 00:18:22,929
Phoenix, get to the LZ now.

235
00:18:23,068 --> 00:18:25,229
Roger, Observer. On my way.

236
00:18:42,087 --> 00:18:44,078
Ethan. I have to talk to you.

237
00:18:44,189 --> 00:18:46,089
- Come on, come on.
- I have to talk to you right now!

238
00:18:46,191 --> 00:18:49,285
