Open up! I need the prisoner!

734
01:05:55,846 --> 01:05:57,245
Oh, my God!

735
01:05:57,948 --> 01:06:00,348
It's really bleeding.
Don't leave me, okay?

736
01:06:00,450 --> 01:06:02,384
Don't worry. I'm right here.

737
01:06:02,486 --> 01:06:04,818
Ethan, there's a G36 in the truck!

738
01:06:04,955 --> 01:06:05,979
I know! I know!

739
01:06:36,420 --> 01:06:39,287
Turn the drone around.
There's an IMF agent in the truck.

740
01:06:47,197 --> 01:06:49,427
Ethan! Get out of the truck!

741
01:06:56,873 --> 01:06:58,306
Ethan, move!

742
01:09:08,772 --> 01:09:11,172
- Hello?
- Rick, this is Ethan. Is Julia home?

743
01:09:11,274 --> 01:09:14,368
Hey, man. Look, I hope you're not mad
I'm here. It's just...

744
01:09:14,478 --> 01:09:15,775
Rick, I'm not mad. Is Julia home?

745
01:09:15,879 --> 01:09:17,813
I tried her cell phone,
and there was no answer.

746
01:09:18,381 --> 01:09:21,976
No. Sorry.
Hey, did your friend find you?

747
01:09:23,787 --> 01:09:25,186
Which friend?

748
01:09:25,322 --> 01:09:27,916
<i>I don't know. Just some English guy.</i>

749
01:09:30,227 --> 01:09:31,592
Rick, what did you tell him?

750
01:09:31,695 --> 01:09:34,562
<i>Look, it's all good, man.
I told him I didn't know where you were,</i>

751
01:09:34,664 --> 01:09:38,122
<i>and Julia might, and he should
just try her at the hospital.</i>

752
01:09:39,836 --> 01:09:40,928
Hello?

753
01:09:47,043 --> 01:09:49,637
- All right, see you tomorrow, Sally.
- All right. Good night, honey.

754
01:09:57,220 --> 01:09:59,620
<i>Hi. It's Julia.
Please leave me a message...</i>

755
01:10:07,197 --> 01:10:11,156
<i>... at 4:00 today, the Chesapeake Bay
Bridge is closed in both directions.</i>

756
01:10:11,268 --> 01:10:13,099
- Sixth floor.
- Sally, this is Ethan.

757
01:10:13,203 --> 01:10:15,262
<i>- I need to talk to Julia.
- Hey, honey.</i>

758
01:10:15,372 --> 01:10:17,067
She just went downstairs.
I'll transfer you.

759
01:10:38,061 --> 01:10:39,255
Damn it!

760
01:10:40,130 --> 01:10:41,188
Excuse me.

761
01:10:41,298 --> 01:10:43,664
I was wondering if you knew
where I might find this patient.

762
01:10:43,767 --> 01:10:46,361
Probably not. But I'll know who can.

763
01:10:51,641 --> 01:10:53,108
What's that?

764
01:11:08,425 --> 01:11:10,359
Sally. Where's Julia?

765
01:11:10,894 --> 01:11:13,260
- Where's Julia?
- I think she left.

766
01:11:13,396 --> 01:11:15,591
Have you tried the east building?

767
01:11:22,138 --> 01:11:24,072
- Has Julia left yet?
- I haven't seen her.

768
01:11:24,174 --> 01:11:26,404
- Mike, Mike. Have you seen Julia?
- Hey, you okay?

769
01:11:26,509 --> 01:11:28,033
- Have you seen Julia?
- No.

770
01:11:32,582 --> 01:11:34,413
Watch it, buddy!

771
01:11:45,095 --> 01:11:47,655
<i>- Jules?
- You hung me outside of an airplane.</i>

772
01:11:47,797 --> 01:11:49,594
<i>You can always tell
someone's character</i>

773
01:11:49,699 --> 01:11:52,224
<i>by the way they treat those
they don't need to treat well.</i>

774
01:11:52,335 --> 01:11:56,237
<i>- If you hurt her, I swear...
- Don't threaten me. Just don't.</i>

775
01:11:56,339 --> 01:12:00,173
<i>The briefcase I picked up in Rome,
the one you took from me,</i>

776
01:12:00,310 --> 01:12:02,403
<i>contains the location
of the Rabbit's Foot.</i>

777
01:12:02,512 --> 01:12:05,913
<i>You're going to get it and bring it to me.
The Rabbit's Foot.</i>

778
01:12:06,016 --> 01:12:08,917
<i>Ethan, you had a watch
last time I saw you.</i>

779
01:12:09,019 --> 01:12:11,783
<i>You have 48 hours,
starting on my mark.</i>

780
01:12:11,888 --> 01:12:13,116
Wait, wait, wait.

781
01:12:13,223 --> 01:12:15,282
<i>Now, call me at this number
when you have it.</i>

782
01:12:15,392 --> 01:12:18,122
<i>- Just wait.
- Julia's life for the Rabbit's Foot.</i>

783
01:12:18,228 --> 01:12:21,629
<i>- You have 48 hours, or she dies.
- Wait! Wait. Wait.</i>

784
01:12:26,336 --> 01:12:28,634
<i>Condition 1-116. All units on scene.</i>

785
01:12:28,738 --> 01:12:30,672
We need you to come with us.

786
01:12:30,807 --> 01:12:33,139
Just... Pete, what the hell is this?

787
01:12:33,243 --> 01:12:35,939
Sorry about that, Mr. Hunt.
We were told to bring you in.

788
01:12:36,046 --> 01:12:38,173
<i>- Okay.
- Get ready to transport.</i>

789
01:12:38,315 --> 01:12:40,078
Whoa. Hey. Just not right now.

790
01:12:40,183 --> 01:12:42,583
- Just tell them you came and that...
- Ethan. Get in.

791
01:12:42,686 --> 01:12:46,053
We don't want to use force here,
and you know we will. Ethan, get in.

792
01:12:46,156 --> 01:12:48,420
- Tell them that you came here...
- Ethan!

793
01:12:48,525 --> 01:12:50,618
...and that I left already, okay?

794
01:12:55,532 --> 01:12:56,726
Freeze!

795
01:12:57,033 --> 01:13:00,161
Ethan, stop! Stop, Ethan!

796
01:13:14,217 --> 01:13:16,014
Yeah. Get his hands.

797
01:13:43,880 --> 01:13:46,849
I reviewed the transcript
of your Berlin operation.

798
01:13:46,950 --> 01:13:48,850
It's very interesting.

799
01:13:48,952 --> 01:13:51,011
It seems that Agent Farris
had some information

800
01:13:51,121 --> 01:13:54,352
she wished to share with you
but not with this agency.

801
01:13:54,457 --> 01:13:56,220
Something you failed to report.

802
01:13:56,326 --> 01:13:59,523
You ordered the Vatican operation
without proper approvals.

803
01:13:59,629 --> 01:14:02,063
That mission
resulted in a catastrophic attack.

804
01:14:02,165 --> 01:14:04,065
And then you fled the scene.

805
01:14:04,167 --> 01:14:07,261
Now, I am not a stranger to disrespect.

806
01:14:08,104 --> 01:14:10,971
You don't get to where I am
without developing a thick skin.

807
01:14:11,074 --> 01:14:13,235
But what I won't stand for,

808
01:14:13,610 --> 01:14:16,875
what I will lose sleep over,
and I love my sleep,

809
01:14:17,180 --> 01:14:20,911
is the idea of an irresponsible
rogue agent working in my office.

810
01:14:21,017 --> 01:14:24,783
So I'm going to
slow things way down here.

811
01:14:28,425 --> 01:14:29,892
You can look at me

812
01:14:29,993 --> 01:14:33,156
with those judgmental,
incriminating eyes all you want,

813
01:14:33,296 --> 01:14:34,957
but I bullshit you not.

814
01:14:35,098 --> 01:14:38,898
I will bleed on the flag
to make sure the stripes stay red.

815
01:14:57,954 --> 01:15:00,252
I don't know what to say to you.

816
01:15:01,458 --> 01:15:04,188
Brassel's right. You're out of control.

817
01:15:05,528 --> 01:15:06,961
Look at me.

818
01:15:08,731 --> 01:15:13,031
Ethan, at least show me the courtesy
of looking at me when I'm talking to you.

819
01:15:21,678 --> 01:15:25,910
I intercepted Davian's call. I know he
wants the Rabbit's Foot for Julia's life.

820
01:15:26,015 --> 01:15:27,482
It's just...

821
01:15:29,886 --> 01:15:31,114
This is

822
01:15:31,921 --> 01:15:33,650
<i>so disappointing.</i>

823
01:15:34,290 --> 01:15:37,726
Go to Shanghai.
Feng Shan Apartments... 1406.

824
01:15:42,665 --> 01:15:46,362
I wish there was something I could do
to help you, but...

825
01:15:51,808 --> 01:15:53,639
Take him to the holding cell.

826
01:17:07,483 --> 01:17:08,916
No, I'm on it.

827
01:17:09,052 --> 01:17:11,145
Yes, sir. There's no need to panic.
I'll get him back.

828
01:17:11,254 --> 01:17:12,312
Sir? Ethan Hunt...

829
01:17:12,422 --> 01:17:13,787
I know what happened.
Give me the radio.

830
01:17:13,890 --> 01:17:16,688
This is Director Brassel. Ethan Hunt
is attempting to escape the building.

831
01:17:16,793 --> 01:17:18,784
He's in the west cargo elevator.
He must be stopped.

832
01:17:18,895 --> 01:17:21,659
I want Mendoza and Graham
in the situation room right away.

833
01:17:21,764 --> 01:17:23,493
I'm having the building surrounded, sir.

834
01:17:23,600 --> 01:17:25,295
I've got units posted
at all the entrances.

835
01:17:25,401 --> 01:17:28,666
<i>This is Brassel again. I'm ordering
a code-six lockdown. I repeat.</i>

836
01:17:28,771 --> 01:17:31,069
- It's Hunt.
- I know it's Hunt.

837
01:17:32,842 --> 01:17:35,572
Hunt was flagged
on sub-basement nine.

838
01:17:35,678 --> 01:17:38,977
I want all security personnel
down there now.

839
01:17:39,515 --> 01:17:41,176
Security channel's jammed.

840
01:17:41,284 --> 01:17:44,378
Hunt must be holding down
the transmit button.

841
01:18:07,944 --> 01:18:09,741
You've got to be kidding me.

842
01:18:20,456 --> 01:18:24,790
<i>Last call for flight 1162 for Helsinki,
now boarding at gate 46.</i>

843
01:18:27,830 --> 01:18:30,526
<i>Final call for Mr. Bower.
Final call for Mr. Bower.</i>

844
01:18:30,633 --> 01:18:32,191
<i>Please come to gate 4.</i>

845
01:18:33,069 --> 01:18:35,970
- Mr. Pavel Sobo... Sobotka.
- Sobotka.

846
01:18:36,072 --> 01:18:39,132
Sobotka. Okay.
And you're flying to Shanghai?

847
01:18:42,645 --> 01:18:46,308
I don't speak Czech. I'm sorry.
Let's see about your flight.

848
01:18:46,416 --> 01:18:47,610
Okay.

849
01:18:47,717 --> 01:18:49,548
- Okay.
- Okay.

850
01:20:27,984 --> 01:20:29,474
Don't kill me.

851
01:20:31,020 --> 01:20:32,351
I'm sorry.

852
01:20:33,723 --> 01:20:35,088
I'm sorry.

853
01:20:36,826 --> 01:20:40,353
Musgrave told us about Julia.
We're here to help.

854
01:20:40,496 --> 01:20:42,589
To get your wife,
you'll need the Rabbit's Foot.

855
01:20:42,698 --> 01:20:44,723
According to the plans
from Davian's briefcase,

856
01:20:44,834 --> 01:20:48,292
it's in a laboratory on the 56th floor
of the Hengshan Lu Building.

857
01:20:48,404 --> 01:20:50,269
Which is a nightmare
for just about every reason.

858
01:20:50,373 --> 01:20:54,002
They're a Chinese military contractor.
We have no pull, no details.

859
01:20:54,143 --> 01:20:55,940
The good news is, whatever it is,

860
01:20:56,045 --> 01:20:58,309
the Rabbit Foot's small,
so we can steal it.

861
01:20:58,414 --> 01:21:01,110
The bad news, we got to steal it.

862
01:21:01,984 --> 01:21:04,646
From a thief's point of view,
this is worst-case scenario.

863
01:21:04,754 --> 01:21:06,949
The security guards
are all privately-contracted

864
01:21:07,056 --> 01:21:08,421
former People's Liberation Army.

865
01:21:08,524 --> 01:21:10,788
The only access to the lab
is by private elevator.

866
01:21:10,893 --> 01:21:13,555
And that can only be activated
by persons inside the lab.

867
01:21:13,663 --> 01:21:16,496
All of it surveilled by
security cameras within the building.

868
01:21:16,599 --> 01:21:18,464
What about the roof?

869
01:21:19,402 --> 01:21:22,166
Four guards full time.
Two on each rooftop.

870
01:21:22,271 --> 01:21:24,068
Langley was a cakewalk
compared to this.

871
01:21:24,173 --> 01:21:25,697
That's the one.

872
01:21:26,609 --> 01:21:28,577
- How tall is that building?
- Why?

873
01:21:28,678 --> 01:21:30,976
It's 162 meters at the highest point.

874
01:21:31,080 --> 01:21:33,514
What about that, the building
on the left? How tall is that one?

875
01:21:33,616 --> 01:21:35,083
Says 226 meters.

876
01:21:35,218 --> 01:21:37,846
226. Distance between the buildings?

877
01:21:37,954 --> 01:21:39,751
47.55 meters across.

878
01:21:56,405 --> 01:21:57,565
Ethan?

879
01:21:58,307 --> 01:22:01,071
That's good. I think it's tall enough.

880
01:22:02,278 --> 01:22:04,712
- For what?
- A fulcrum.

881
01:22:06,816 --> 01:22:09,512
Oh, you're gonna swing...
No, no, no, no. Wait, wait.

882
01:22:09,619 --> 01:22:12,019
- You could bounce right off the roof.
- Yes, I could.

883
01:22:12,121 --> 01:22:14,248
Even if you made it to the rooftop,
took out the guards,

884
01:22:14,357 --> 01:22:17,986
and got the Rabbit's Foot, you can't just
walk out of the lobby. What's your exit?

885
01:22:18,094 --> 01:22:19,721
Base-jump off the top. I need a chute.

886
01:22:19,829 --> 01:22:22,024
Even at 162, you're pushing
minimum height for a jump.

887
01:22:22,131 --> 01:22:23,689
Chute opens any lower than that
and you're dead.

888
01:22:23,799 --> 01:22:24,857
What are you going to do?

889
01:22:24,967 --> 01:22:27,060
Land in the middle of Shanghai
and hope no one notices?

890
01:22:27,169 --> 01:22:28,431
Central Park's two blocks away.

891
01:22:28,537 --> 01:22:30,437
Wait, wait, Ethan, I'm not saying
I have a better idea,

892
01:22:30,539 --> 01:22:33,007
but there's a point
where bold becomes stupid.

893
01:22:33,109 --> 01:22:35,577
Now, we don't even know
what this thing is, and you're talking

894
01:22:35,678 --> 01:22:38,545
about handing it over to a guy
who provides terrorists with information.

895
01:22:38,648 --> 01:22:40,741
Luther, of course I'm not
suggesting that we just hand it over.

896
01:22:40,850 --> 01:22:43,717
We're going to tag the Rabbit's Foot
so we can trace it and know where it is.

897
01:22:43,819 --> 01:22:46,720
Now, you know we can get
that gear here. I just deliver it myself.

898
01:22:46,822 --> 01:22:49,689
We contact Musgrave,
have the IMF trace a tag, order a raid,

899
01:22:49,792 --> 01:22:51,555
get the Rabbit's Foot back, grab Davian.

900
01:22:51,661 --> 01:22:54,357
Now, if I get out with Julia, we win.

901
01:22:55,498 --> 01:22:57,261
If I don't, then...

902
01:23:03,673 --> 01:23:06,540
Look, then she's dead anyway.
And so am I.

903
01:23:07,743 --> 01:23:09,040
You know?

904
01:23:09,178 --> 01:23:13,512
Goddamn it, it's 8:11, it's 8:12.

905
01:23:16,018 --> 01:23:19,146
And we have two hours
before they kill my wife.

906
01:23:20,056 --> 01:23:21,785
Are you in or not?

907
01:23:29,365 --> 01:23:31,060
Of course we're in.

908
01:24:03,399 --> 01:24:05,162
You got 18 minutes.

909
01:24:07,570 --> 01:24:09,470
You're going to make it over there.

910
01:24:09,572 --> 01:24:12,905
You're going to find the Rabbit's Foot,
get back to the roof,

911
01:24:13,042 --> 01:24:14,839
radio me when you're ready to make
the jump,

912
01:24:14,944 --> 01:24:17,378
and we're going to come get you.

913
01:24:18,381 --> 01:24:20,110
Thank you for coming.

914
01:24:20,883 --> 01:24:22,350
That's my job.

915
01:24:58,654 --> 01:24:59,985
Batter up.

916
01:25:27,783 --> 01:25:30,809
Oh, yeah. They're freaking out.
Hit them again.

917
01:27:05,714 --> 01:27:06,840
Okay.

918
01:27:08,384 --> 01:27:09,373
<i>He made it.</i>

919
01:27:09,585 --> 01:27:10,950
He made it.

920
01:27:14,089 --> 01:27:15,852
I knew he'd make it.

921
01:27:30,406 --> 01:27:33,307
I'm going in. I'll be out in five minutes.

922
01:27:41,483 --> 01:27:43,883
- It's been 12 minutes.
- He's got five minutes left.

923
01:27:43,986 --> 01:27:47,422
If he doesn't call Davian in five minutes,
Julia's dead.

924
01:27:47,523 --> 01:27:48,888
<i>Anything?</i>

925
01:27:50,459 --> 01:27:51,448
Negative.

926
01:27:51,594 --> 01:27:53,721
<i>How about you? Any good news?</i>

927
01:27:53,829 --> 01:27:55,262
No, nothing.

928
01:27:55,431 --> 01:27:56,921
Come on, Ethan.

929
01:28:06,208 --> 01:28:07,675
What is that?

930
01:28:12,848 --> 01:28:17,148
When I was little I had a cat,
and he used to run away all the time.

931
01:28:18,654 --> 01:28:21,782
And it's just a prayer I'd say
to bring him home.

932
01:28:23,726 --> 01:28:25,250
Teach it to me.

933
01:28:27,029 --> 01:28:29,224
<i>I've got the Rabbit's Foot,
but I can't make it to the roof.</i>

934
01:28:29,331 --> 01:28:32,129
What the hell do you mean you can't
make it to the roof? Where are you?

935
01:28:32,234 --> 01:28:34,293
<i>Look up! Look up, look up!</i>

936
01:28:37,172 --> 01:28:39,333
- Oh, shit.
- He's way too low.

937
01:30:30,119 --> 01:30:33,111
- Ethan! Get in! They're coming!
- Who?

938
01:30:33,255 --> 01:30:35,883
Building security, and they're pissed.

939
01:30:38,494 --> 01:30:40,325
Okay. Go, go, go, go.

940
01:30:47,202 --> 01:30:49,295
How much time you got left?

941
01:30:49,605 --> 01:30:51,402
Less than two minutes.

942
01:30:57,713 --> 01:31:00,841
You gotta get us out of here.
I lost the signal.

943
01:31:03,552 --> 01:31:05,315
- You okay?
- Not yet.

944
01:31:13,695 --> 01:31:14,821
Come on. Come on.

945
01:31:22,237 --> 01:31:23,864
I don't have a signal.
I don't have a signal.

946
01:31:23,972 --> 01:31:25,166
I'm on it. I'm on it. I'm on it!

947
01:31:33,649 --> 01:31:34,707
Zhen!

948
01:31:36,852 --> 01:31:38,479
Damn it. I'm sorry.

949
01:31:46,728 --> 01:31:48,389
Put pressure on it.

950
01:31:48,897 --> 01:31:52,025
- Tell me when you get a signal.
- What are you doing?

951
01:32:11,119 --> 01:32:12,677
I got a signal!

952
01:32:17,025 --> 01:32:18,322
Hit redial.

953
01:32:20,462 --> 01:32:23,158
<i>You only had five seconds left.
Do you realize that?</i>

954
01:32:23,265 --> 01:32:25,563
The Rabbit's Foot. I have it.

955
01:32:25,934 --> 01:32:29,927
<i>The train yard at Dunan Zhong Lu.
Wait for me there. Alone.</i>

956
01:32:33,242 --> 01:32:34,709
<i>- Yeah?
- Go secure.</i>

957
01:32:34,810 --> 01:32:36,038
We are.

958
01:32:37,145 --> 01:32:39,170
<i>I have the Rabbit's Foot.</i>

959
01:32:39,281 --> 01:32:41,511
- You okay?
- I'm tagging it now.

960
01:32:44,486 --> 01:32:46,852
You need to run a trace.
Make sure we have eyes on this thing.

961
01:32:46,955 --> 01:32:49,924
- What's the tag?
- 6-3-9-6-4-1.

962
01:32:50,893 --> 01:32:52,053
Got it.

963
01:32:54,796 --> 01:32:56,127
I see you on Luang Tao Lu Road.

964
01:32:56,231 --> 01:32:59,723
If you don't hear from me in eight hours,
you send an army after this thing.

965
01:32:59,835 --> 01:33:01,700
- Good luck.
- You, too.

966
01:33:09,111 --> 01:33:10,908
<i>- Mr. Musgrave.
- Yeah.</i>

967
